==Syntax==
*[[countitem]](<itemid>);
*[[countitem]]("Itemname");

==Description==

Countitem will return the number of items of <itemid> the invoking player holds in his inventory.<br>
Like in [[getitem]], you can also write the name of the item ("Name"-column in ItemDB).<br>

==Example==

<pre>
mes "You have "+countitem(501)+"Apples!";
close;
</pre>Will print out the number of Apples the char holds...
<pre>
if(countitem("Apple")>=5){
 mes "This will only print if you have 5 or more Apples!";
 close;
}
</pre>

